reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The SanDisk 256GB Ultra Dual Drive Go USB Type-C Flash Drive is an absolute gem when it comes to portable storage solutions. This tiny device has completely transformed the way I transfer and manage my data. The compact and lightweight design makes it incredibly convenient to carry around, whether it's in my pocket, bag, or even on a keychain. With the dual USB Type-C and USB Type-A connectors, I can effortlessly connect it to a wide range of devices, including laptops, smartphones, and tablets. The versatility of this flash drive is unmatched, and it has become an indispensable tool in my digital life.What truly sets the SanDisk Ultra Dual Drive Go apart is its impressive functionality. With a generous storage capacity of 256GB, I no longer have to worry about running out of space for my files, documents, photos, and videos. The high-speed USB 3.1 performance ensures that my data transfers are quick and efficient, saving me valuable time. The SanDisk Memory Zone app further enhances the functionality by providing an intuitive interface to manage and organize my files across different devices. It's incredibly user-friendly and has made the entire process seamless and hassle-free.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just What I Needed
reviews.reviewText: I recently received a replacement for my phone. They gave me a Samsung Galaxy S215G phone. Unfortunately, this phone does not come with a micro SD slot. Therefore, I needed to purchase something for additional storage (I take a lot of pictures and videos). A friend suggested the 512GB Flashdrive. This is just the right size. It is small, and can be used both ways (C-side and USB-side). I have not tried the USB side, yet, but I did use the C-side for my phone, and then for my laptop. Works like a charm. It also has a little slot so I can put it on my keychain. I highly recommend this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Is Cheap, Feels Cheap
reviews.reviewText: It's a 13 dollar flash drive. Cheap flimsy plastic build, doesn't feel like it will last. About as much as one can expect for 13 dollars. Works well as a flash drive though, really like the dual USB C/A. I recommend, but don't expect quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very tiny and works )
reviews.reviewText: Write speed is a little bit slow, but for gadgets I can recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great product. Compact size and double USB sizes
reviews.reviewText: This little USB is great. I can use on my android phone for transferring to a PC or just onto the stick to save files. I would not recommend as a constant-use device. It's so small that it gets really hot if you keep it plugged in and run your files directly off of it. I use it for transferring and storing and it's been great! I use a larger SanDisk usb that has better heat dissipation when I'm running files or programs from the USB stick.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fast and Practical
reviews.reviewText: Once SanDisk App is installed the drive works seamlessly and offers options of copying, moving or deleting files and other apps on the phone. Very fast. One gripe is the construction material is made of thin plastic, especially on the USB-A side, which does not seem to be all that durable. It's a fast and practical solution moving files between devices.
